goals.question: What is the relationship between X and Series?
goals.visualization: Box plot of X by Series
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify any differences in the distribution of X across different categories of Series.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['X'], data['Y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['X'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['X'].median()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Y'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Y'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Y'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_datetime(data['X'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='X')
    plt.plot(data['X'], data['Y'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of X over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X'] = pd.to_numeric(data['X'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['X'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Series'] == s]['X'] for s in data['Series'].unique()], labels=data['Series'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Series')
    ax.set_ylabel('X')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between X and Series?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
